3 And since a great union of this sort is secured chiefly by the hond qs Obedience; this must ever be maintained in all its vigour: And those who are sent forth from the Houses to labour in the Lord’s harvest, should be well exercised therein‚ as far as possi- ble : and in this virtue, such as take the lead in the Society should outshine the rest in their good example 3 and always in harmony with their Superior should persovere promptly, humbly and devotedly in their obedience to him.
